---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About SMS API Compare | Independent Provider Comparisons"
  description="Learn about SMS API Compare — an independent comparison platform helping developers and businesses find the best SMS API provider."
>
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900">About SMS API Compare</h1>

    <div class="mt-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Who We Are</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        SMS API Compare is an independent comparison platform. We are <strong>not affiliated with any SMS API provider</strong> — our goal is to give developers and businesses the unbiased information they need to make the right choice.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Our Mission</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        Choosing an SMS API provider can be overwhelming. Pricing structures vary wildly, feature sets differ in subtle but important ways, and compliance requirements add another layer of complexity. Our mission is to help developers and businesses cut through the noise and choose the best SMS API for their specific needs.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">What We Compare</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        We evaluate SMS API providers across the dimensions that matter most:
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-3 list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 leading-relaxed space-y-2">
        <li><strong>Pricing</strong> — per-message costs, phone number fees, volume discounts, and hidden charges</li>
        <li><strong>Features</strong> — two-way messaging, MMS, shortcodes, global coverage, and delivery reporting</li>
        <li><strong>Compliance</strong> — TCPA, 10DLC registration, carrier requirements, and opt-out handling</li>
        <li><strong>Developer Experience</strong> — SDK quality, documentation, API design, and ease of integration</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Our Data</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        All comparison data is researched from official provider sources — documentation, pricing pages, and published API references. We update our data regularly to ensure accuracy, though pricing and features can change at any time. We always recommend verifying current details directly with the provider before making a purchasing decision.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">How We Make Money</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        Transparency matters to us. SMS API Compare is monetized through advertising and referral links. When you click a link to a provider and sign up, we may earn a commission at no additional cost to you. This funding allows us to keep the site running and our comparisons up to date. Importantly, <strong>affiliate relationships never influence our rankings or recommendations</strong>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Our Commitment</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        We believe in neutral, data-driven comparisons. Every provider is evaluated using the same criteria, and we present the facts so you can make an informed decision. If you spot an error or have feedback, we encourage you to <a href="/contact" class="text-primary hover:underline">get in touch</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
